## Test Generation Strategy

### From GWT Specifications

```gherkin
Given {precondition}
When {action}
Then {outcome}
```

Becomes:

```cpp
TEST(TaskQueueTest, {ScenarioName}) {
    // Given
    {Setup precondition}
    
    // When
    {Execute action}
    
    // Then
    EXPECT_{condition};
    EXPECT_{condition};
}
```

### Coverage Target per FR
- Minimum 1 positive test
- Minimum 1 boundary test
- Minimum 1 error test
- Edge cases as appropriate

## Verification Checklist

- [ ] All FRs have implementing code
- [ ] All FRs have test coverage
- [ ] Line coverage ≥ 80%
- [ ] Branch coverage ≥ 70%
- [ ] All @require tags valid
- [ ] All @adr tags valid
- [ ] No compilation warnings
- [ ] No static analysis errors
- [ ] Performance benchmarks pass
- [ ] Security scan clean
- [ ] Integration tests pass
- [ ] Documentation complete

## Guidelines

### Coverage Interpretation
- 90-100%: Excellent
- 80-90%: Good (minimum acceptable)
- 70-80%: Needs improvement
- <70%: Insufficient

### Traceability Verification
```python
def verify_traceability():
    for fr in all_requirements:
        # Forward trace
        code = find_implementing_code(fr)
        test = find_test(fr)
        
        assert code is not None, f"{fr} has no implementation"
        assert test is not None, f"{fr} has no test"
        
        # Backward trace
        for code_file in all_source_files:
            tags = extract_requirement_tags(code_file)
            assert all_valid(tags), f"{code_file} has invalid tags"
            
        for test_file in all_test_files:
            fr_refs = extract_tested_requirements(test_file)
            assert all_valid(fr_refs), f"{test_file} tests unknown FRs"
```

## Human Review

Present to user:
1. Executive summary (pass/fail)
2. Coverage dashboard
3. Critical issues (if any)
4. Recommendation

User decides:
- **CERTIFY**: Accept as complete
- **FIX**: Address issues and re-run
- **WAIVE**: Accept with known issues

## Completion Criteria
- All tests generated and passing
- Coverage meets minimum thresholds
- Traceability is complete
- No critical issues
- Certification report generated
- Project ready for production